com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api.statement
Interface SwitchStatement

All Superinterfaces:
JSOM, Statement, StatementBlockElement, StatementBlockElementContainer
public interface SwitchStatement
extends Statement, StatementBlockElementContainer

This Statement type represents a switch statement.

This interface also defines an inner interface SwitchLabel representing case and default.

Problem: SwitchLabel extends StatementBlockElementContainer and therefore each SwitchLabel knows about the statements and local class and variable declarations that have been stated following this SwitchLabel up to the next one or up to the end of the switch statement for the last SwitchLabel. However, this doesn't actually match the visibility of the content in the real Java world because SwitchLabels haven't their own local scopes - there's only one local scope bound to the switch statement. Solution: Also SwitchStatement extends StatementBlockElementContainer but an implementation mustn't have it's own content but operate on the statement block element content of the SwitchLabels instead.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

getSwitchLabels

java.util.List<SwitchStatement.SwitchLabel> getSwitchLabels(java.util.List<SwitchStatement.SwitchLabel> pList)
Returns a list of the case and default clauses.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the case and default clauses will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of case and/or default clauses. If there are no case and default clauses null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.
